caption: My mango lassi didn’t taste like one. Awful couldn’t even drink half of it. Threw it away. My boyfriend got the pink smoothie which he also threw out. Tastes like they put ice in the smoothies. We had to wait outside for our food which was cold outside. Won’t be coming back.
Absolutely incredible, the quality of the ingredients and the way they are prepared. Way beyond expectations. Highly recommended!
Excellent and fantastic food! Healthy never tasted so good.
one of the freshest, most delicious, customizable salads i have ever had.  well worth the price and when i am in portland this is at the top of my list.
I've always enjoyed everything I've ever ordered at LB Kitchen (very into the kale caesar) but I just tried the Classy Chip Cookie for the first time and it is mindblowing. Thanks LB Kitchen!
Fave spot in Portland! LB Kitchen makes it easy for vegans to find healthy & hearty meal options — so grateful! <3
LB sandwich($10) is the best one in all Portland, Maine
Food was excellent and coffee was great. Will come here again, might even buy it. Just kidding, I paid.
Nourishing food that helped heal me after sickness, truly thankful for this spot.
This is one of my all time favorites in portland. So friendly. Love the healthy vibe. Butterfly mint lattes and delicious gluten free baked goods. The breakfast salad is amazing. Thanks LB kitchen!
Fantastic! The Keto is the best salad I've ever had.

I’ll be real: Hit the SPOT Big salads, flavorful and fresh. Got the Bahn Mi and added chicken for $4.50. Yum. Harissa Hash was decent too! Super quick. Two salads cost $33, so when you feel like splurging, this is the place *COVID only takeout +Quick +Flavorful -Tad expensive
Love this place, my favorite things are their Bahn Mi bowl and Breakfast Salad.  Also the pancakes are yummy.  Wonderful staff and service.

LB Kitchen is delicious! Staff and food are both amazing! I frequent this location for items such as the Keto Bowl, Harissa Hash and Purple Rain smoothies just to name a few! Ive never had a bad food experience which means they are consistent with their food. Thoughtful, healthy and tasty options! Gluten Free and Vegan/Vegetarian Options!
Place is lights out! To interpret my lingo, this place is amazing. Great, quality food. All sorts of options.
Delicious food, I ordered the LB sandwich, had just the right amount of everything.  We will be back, super happy.
Our daughter brought lunch to us from LB Kitchen and absolutely everything was delicious! So fresh, tasty and delicious. Yum.

Absolutely worth a visit for tourists coming to Portland and for locals! LB Kitchen was suggested by our AirBnB hosts nearby and this turned out to be our favorite restaurant in the Portland area. The nitro cold brew coffee is truly wonderful and worth the visit for any coffee enthusiast. The menu caters to a wide range of dietary needs, not just vegans and vegetarians. Dishes are affordable and well worth it compared to big name restaurants in the area. We visited KB Kitchen  daily during our three day stint in Portland and highly recommend giving it a try!
Friendly helpful service, DELICIOUS healthy food, filling hearty meal for a fair price. 7/5 stars
Breakfast was so good, so fresh, so worth it!!
Love the purple rain smoothie and adding a piece of wild salmon to my salad or sandwich in the morning! Outstanding quality.
The LB breakfast sandwich (+ egg) is perfection.
The Keto bowl! ‘Nuff said 😋👍🏾👍🏾👍🏾
Awesome ❤️
There's not a day that goes by when I don't crave a bowl from LB Kitchen. The Keto is simple and fresh- and so, so good.
Great spot with an awesome menu, seating was a bit difficult. There was not a lot of room, but overall great experience!
So yum. And good for ya. Top quality. Innovative. Delicious!
Refreshing healthy options. Amazing pancakes and avocado toast!!
Super tasty and healthy breakfast. Perfect portion size, cute place and cozy atmosphere.
Orders a tofu sandwich they put bacon on it... Also two sandwiches and two coffees cost me close to $40

Had curry with chicken, the curry was bland, nearly unseasoned, the lack of flavor and no layering of spices make the entire meal inedible. 2 stars instead of 1 because they offered to make something else. I did not take them up on it due to being put off by the entire meal.
Great menu and food! A little tight with not a ton of seats. Unique place, love the Speckled Ax coffee!
Unbelievably great breakfast. So fresh and the Gluten free options are fantastic. Very nice staff as well.
Great food and super accommodating for allergies. Friendly staff too. Will definitely come back!
One of my favorite spots for breakfast and lunch in Portland. Really eclectic menu with lots of healthy options. Love their bowls!
My family just had our first meal at LB and loved it!  It's hard to find good vegetarian breakfast/ brunch spots but this is the place in Portland ME.  We will definitely be back soon!
(Translated by Google) In the area a very good place to have breakfast in a relaxed atmosphere.  (Original) In der Gegend ein sehr guter Ort, um in entspannter Atmosphäre gut zu frühstücken.
Amazing place to visit
Super delicious breakfast!
Amazing food! I love the salmon and kale bowl and the harissa hash. Smoothies and nitro cold brew are great too. Great menu and great execution.

I tried the eggs and toast. Very simple yet the food quality was better than most. They use locally sourced products and provide vegan and gluten free options. They still serve eggs and bacon as well. I'll be back to try more.
Fresh food, great taste, lovely staff.
Loved the variety and quality of options vegan or high quality meat options and enough drink options that you can fill your need

Very hip and trendy. The bowls were satisfying and filling. It was a great break from the traditional fried-food shacks. Only complaint is that...to sit outside, you have to walk around the building. Odd...but I understand.
Very yummy, great vibe, just wish were around longer to try more of the goodness.
Delicious, unique, healthy. The waffle was perhaps the best I’ve ever eaten.
Delicious!

The fresh salad with fried egg and pickled veggies was delightful and exactly what I wanted. I usually get the Keto, which is AMAZING, but I changed it up tried this salad and a new drink for me called The Mint. I think I found a new favorite drink as well! Oat milk, butterfly pea flower tea, mint and other magical igredients make a delicious and refreshing beverage. The staff are always pleasant and helpful. The garage widows open to look out over the harbor view park. I sat and enjoyed my delicious items with a breeze from the water and the sun at me back.

Food was amazing at this gem. We stopped on our way through for a business trip. Super accommodating with food allergies! Had the LB sandwich and my colleague had the harissa hash. Both amazing. Definitely will stop on the next business trip.
Cool lol place with employees who smile big!
Delicious Bowls, but unfortunately the portion was not so big. They serve a very strong (and sour) Espresso.
Fresh & healthy! Portions were large too (we both got bowls and had tons of leftovers). Definitely a little small inside, but manageable.

When we went they weren’t serving their full menu due to unforeseen circumstance which was fine. We ordered the basic sandwich and the green machine smoothie. Sandwich was great but unfortunately found a small black hair (not matching our own) in the smoothie
Very good food
Delicious pancake and latte

They have great vegetarian selection, serve breakfast all day and has Root Wild kombucha which is the best. Had the All The Vegetables bowl with Pesto Farro and it was very flavorful. Everything on the menu sounds so good and I will definitely go back to try other things. The place is small but has plenty of tables and a great vibe. They sell cute t-shirts but too expensive ($25).
Solid food. Solid variety.

Feel very fortunate to have discovered LB Kitchen.  They offer many healthy, well thought out options.  Everything we ordered was great - Keto bowl, Sweet and Salty oats, Avocado toast, Mint drink.  Very helpful, friendly staff and food came out quickly.
Food ok, so crammed into tight seating it was difficult to have a conversation. Service was friendly but only went so far to meet dietary needs.

Was recommended this spot by the concierge at the Press Hotel and could not be happier with my breakfast choice!  Location was extremely accessible by foot, the staff was extremely friendly, the food was incredible, and the cold brew was everything I needed it to be after a long day and night.  Highly recommend their version of Avocado Toast with a fried egg!  Put this on your list of places to grab a healthy breakfast if in the Portland area!

MY FAVORITE PLACE!!! I don't know how to even describe how great the food was. I highly suggest trying a smoothie as well. The interior was so cute and the staff was very chill for how busy they were. Only thing is it's very small inside and tough to find a good spot to sit.

I appreciate how the staff here is friendly and happy to see its customers, which is becoming rare in Portland.  The food is healthy and really good.  The veggie bowl and chicken stock are just delicious.  Eat well and feel welcome.
Really good food! The purple rain smoothie was amazing!
Food was good, but service was less than ideal  They ask for tip, yet do not serve you and you have to do your own dishes.....  Don’t Tip!!!!
One of my favorite places to eat in Portland. Amazing vegan options, gluten free stuff, and well-sourced meats.
Gluten free pancakes - hallelujah! 🙏🏽

Avocado toast with truffle oil, add a fried egg & bacon. They have a patio out back. Friendly service. Will probably only go after pay day, because somehow everything I order here ends up being $15+ for just myself, but it's always been worth it.
This place is welcoming, healthy, and has many options to choose from. Recommend Sassy & Savory oats, fuels the soul with flavor and warmth! Various coffee options kept our group happy as well.
love this food. love the people making this food. ❤️
Very tasty, creative, healthy food. Bright bustling atmosphere and quick service.
Delicious healthy oatmeal with interesting toppings, an amazing smoothie with blueberries,acia and bee pollen! Plus bacon and eggs for hubby in a sunny window seat. Nice friendly staff, thanks!

Cozy little healthy/comfort bistro where the wait staff is friendly, the coffee is good and hot and the LB Sandwich is flat-out delicious. I'm already daydreaming about the next time I can munch on one!
Healthy food and relax ambiance

It can be tough to be a vegetarian in Portland- lots of seafood and not always the healthiest veg options. I was stoked to stumble across this place. Great vegetarian, vegan, and gluten free options. Good portion sizes and reasonable pricing. Such a nice change of pace to have options on a menu. Keep up the good work!!

Food was good, but the maple syrup was not real. This is so disappointing.  The rest of menu was very intentionally natural and very in style, but as a connoisseur of maple syrup, the sticky substance served was FAKE.
Love this local establishment. The food is fresh, healthy, and always delicious!

I'm a regular member of the clean plate club but this place has me pacing myself because I just wanted to eat everything way too fast. I had the avocado toast with an egg on top. Crazy delicious avocado mash. Cozy atmosphere with lots of natural light. It's an excellent way to start the morning. Also, I love that you get to order at the counter and pay for your food in advance, I know that plenty of places do this but I always love it when I'm not having to wait on a check after finishing a delicious meal. It just makes it that much easier to stay in the moment either with your friends or a book or maybe just your own thoughts. I'll be back for sure.

Their philosophy centers on food-as-medicine, which comes through in each of their dishes. Their soothing tumeric bone broth is wonderful on a sore throat! Can get crowded between 12-2pm, may have to wait for a table.
Best healthy, delicious breakfast in Portland
Avocado addiction toast is the best I've ever had. I can't even come close to making this at home.
What a great place for lunch.  Fresh ingredients.  The LB Sandwich add a fried egg is my favorite.

Super cool little place towards the East end serving delicious health-oriented foods from a small counter. I had a hot drink with a blue spirulina that was a color I've never seen before, and an oatmeal that was one of the most delicious I've ever had. Sweet and salty I think it was called. Really unique flavors that worked so well together.
Healthy food. Slow service.
Fresh food, original ideas!
Fantastic cafe! The "Blue" Matcha, Breakfast Salad and Avo Toast were delicious.
The Bánh mì is the best in Portland!
Great food there!
favorite veggie place in Portland. good coffee.
Tasty & health focused food. Plenty of veggie & vegan options. Will be back!
Great little spot, lots of gluten free and vegan options.
If you want delightful breakfast in a bright and friendly environment, LB Kitchen is your jam. I'm in love with ordering avacado addiction and savoring it on the patio out back.

The cutest spot with the most amazing food!! My boyfriend and I both LOVED our breakfast and drinks. It’s great that they provide local, high-quality items on their menu.  I am dairy and gluten free and they were very accommodating. I definitely recommend the All Veg bowl and the Golden Milk!

Not cheap, but top notch ingredients! I would rather pay $3 more for this quality of food. Incredibly fresh, very flavorful, and so many options for me! I am allergic to dairy so being able to eat a Caeser salad, or noodles with pesto is such a treat. No dairy! Tons of flavor! I like to add salmon to my lunch choices. I recommend the bone broth in the winter. The staff has been friendly, polite, and relaxed.
Visited LB Kitchen on my way to Main, Bar Harbor. It was easy to find a parking, quite place, nice vegetarian and vegan options, good smoothie, self service.
Everything was delicious. Grain bowl for lunch and avocado toast with egg added for breakfast and matcha latte.
Salad was delicious.
Amazing delicious food from Chloe
Small but the food is great.  I enjoyed their variety of toasts.  Tandoori popcorn to go was a good idea.

Really great bowls and friendly staff. It is a small space so you may need to share a table. I would recommend this spot and plan on coming back to try more of the menu. The Tofu Bahn Mí bowl was delicious as was the iced matcha latte.
The Figa with boar redang ( a meat based red curry) was amazing. The complex spicing delicious. The Curry, with butternut squash, was just the right hot. Loved it! Will be back.
Good coffee. Going back tomorrow for breakfast and will update the review.

This place is phenomenal! It’s clean and inviting as you walk in. The people behind the counter are kind.  The menu is creative and offers something for all walks of life. I’ve eaten here several times and have enjoyed it more and more everytime. If you eat meat just order the Figa it’s so perfectly done.
Yes! Refreshingly healthy options for breakfast/brunch that are so delicious! And it's a really wonderful, chill, welcoming atmosphere.

Healthy, fresh, and certainly hip. Worth a visit if you're into the organic/vegan/vegetarian scene. The Saturday bowl was a great brunch item but pretty pricey; LB Kitchen is definitely not cheap. Lukewarm is a good word to describe the service and the atmosphere was very hands-off and casual. This place is great if you're big on organic/all-natural or vegan/vegetarian and don't mind spending a little extra for good food that'll agree with your diet, but can be skipped by anyone else.

Really good food here. High quality ingredients, they do most things (like pickling/curing) in house. Portions aren't huge, but you're getting amazing, healthy, thoughtful food.  We stop each time we drive near Portland.
Adorable and phenomenal food. Unique and very healthful combinations of delicious foods. Love their "bowls" of goodness. Bone broth and matcha tea are excellent!! Thanks LB
Delicious and healthy! Loved every bite
sweet, quaint & really delicious!
Great breakfast/lunch bowls, and everything they do is well made. New patio is a special treat.

I was really excited to eat here because we heard great things and that they offer healthy/vegan breakfast options. The atmosphere was cozy but the service was lukewarm and the prices a little steep. We had the avocado toast which was delicious and the vegan chocolate chip cookies which were also good. They serve Tandem coffee which is delicious. The service is the only thing that I would say left to be desired.
Phenomenal! The chicken bone broth will fix what ails ya...The carrot cake will turn that frown upside down...and the staff will keep it that way!!! LOVE LOVE LOVE!
Fresh, healthy, delicious and the place is adorable!
Friendly, relaxed, delicious, healthy - need I say more???

An awesome new spot in town for a bright, healthy breakfast with tons of flavor! A lot of different options for breakfast and lunch (avocado toasts, breakfast salads, broths!) makes this a definite place to check out. I also found their smoothies to be excellent!
